%description:
Deterministic MLDv1 router/querier behavior test (RFC 2710 §6).

Tests the router/querier state machine with fixed RNG seed and short timers so
all RTR-01..05 behaviors are observable within a 15s simulation.
Membership is driven by real apps (UdpSink with multicastGroup), the production path.

RTR-01 (periodic General Query):
  The router has multicastForwarding=true (set at node level so
  NetworkLayerNodeBase propagates to the routing table). With
  startupQueryInterval=1s the router sends its first General Listener Query on
  each multicast-capable interface at ~t=1s. Subsequent periodic Queries fire
  at queryInterval=5s. The %contains assertion matches the first General Query.

RTR-02 (listener recorded on Report):
  host1 runs UdpSink with multicastGroup="ff0e::1:2:3".  The socket join at
  t=0 fires ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal -> Mldv1::multicastGroupJoined ->
  unsolicited Report sent.  The router receives it and records the listener via
  addMulticastListener (NO_LISTENERS_PRESENT -> LISTENERS_PRESENT). The test
  asserts both the "received Multicast Listener Report" and "recorded listener"
  EV_INFO markers.

RTR-03 (Done -> MAS Query):
  host1's UdpSink has stopTime=5s. Socket close fires ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal ->
  Mldv1::multicastGroupLeft -> Multicast Listener Done (type=132) to ff02::2.
  The router receives it and sends a Multicast-Address-Specific Query for
  ff0e::1:2:3, then starts the last-listener countdown (lastListenerQueryInterval=1s,
  lastListenerQueryCount=2). With no Reply, the leave timer expires and the group
  is removed (removeMulticastListener, NO_LISTENERS_PRESENT).

RTR-04 (per-(if,group) router state machine):
  Observable via the RTR-02 and RTR-03 markers: NO_LISTENERS_PRESENT ->
  LISTENERS_PRESENT (recorded listener on Report) -> CHECKING_LISTENERS (Done) ->
  NO_LISTENERS_PRESENT (leave timer expiry).

RTR-05 (configurable timing params):
  All router timer parameters are overridden to short values in the INI, verified
  implicitly by the test completing within the 15s sim-time-limit.

HOST-ONLY NEGATIVE (single-querier proof):
  host1 has multicastForwarding=false (the default). Only the router runs the
  querier path. A %postrun-command extracts any Query-sending lines from host1
  and a %not-contains asserts the list is empty, proving a
  multicastForwarding=false node never becomes a querier.

Network: host1 (StandardHost6) and router (Router6) connect via a shared
EthernetHub. Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator assigns addresses. Both nodes have
hasMld=true. RNG seed is fixed for reproducibility.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetHub;
import inet.node.ipv6.Router6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network MldRouterBasicNetwork
{
    types:
        channel ethline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
        host1: StandardHost6;
        router: Router6;
        hub: EthernetHub;
    connections:
        host1.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        router.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../src
network = MldRouterBasicNetwork
sim-time-limit = 15s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "

# Fix RNG seed for deterministic behavior of uniform(0, maxRespTime) in startHostTimer
seed-set = 0

eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

# Enable MLD on all nodes so they can receive inbound Reports/Dones
**.ipv6.hasMld = true
# Disable DAD for fast startup (no 1s+ delay before addresses become ready)
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 10

# RTR-01: activate the real querier ONLY on the router.
# Must be set at the node (Router6) level: NetworkLayerNodeBase propagates
#   *.multicastForwarding = this.multicastForwarding
# to all submodules (including ipv6.routingTable), so a per-submodule INI
# setting would be silently overridden by the node-level default(false).
**.router.multicastForwarding = true

# RTR-01 timers: shorten query intervals for a fast deterministic run.
# The router fires its first General Query at startupQueryInterval after init.
**.router.ipv6.mld.startupQueryInterval = 1s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryInterval = 5s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryResponseInterval = 1s
# RTR-03/04 last-listener timers: short so group removal is observable within 15s.
**.router.ipv6.mld.lastListenerQueryInterval = 1s
**.router.ipv6.mld.lastListenerQueryCount = 2
# multicastListenerInterval: keep a group alive this long without a Report.
**.router.ipv6.mld.multicastListenerInterval = 6s

# RTR-02: host1 joins ff0e::1:2:3 via UdpSink (fires ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal -> unsolicited Report).
**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host1.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1:2:3"
# RTR-03: host1 leaves at t=5s via socket close (fires ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal -> Done).
**.host1.app[0].stopTime = 5s

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTR-01: router sends the first periodic General Listener Query
%contains: stdout
MldRouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending General Listener Query on iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTR-02: router receives host1's unsolicited Report for ff0e::1:2:3
%contains: stdout
MldRouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTR-02: router records the listener (NO_LISTENERS_PRESENT -> LISTENERS_PRESENT)
%contains: stdout
MldRouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: recorded listener for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTR-03: router receives host1's Done for ff0e::1:2:3 (from socket close at t=5s)
%contains: stdout
MldRouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# RTR-03: router sends a Multicast-Address-Specific Query on receiving the Done
%contains: stdout
MldRouterBasicNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group=ff0e::1:2:3 on iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-ONLY NEGATIVE (single-querier activation proof):
%# host1 has multicastForwarding=false (the default) and must NEVER send any Query.
%# Extract all host1 Query-sending lines; the resulting file must be empty.
%postrun-command: grep -E "MldRouterBasicNetwork\.host1\.ipv6\.mld: Mldv1: sending (General Listener|Multicast-Address-Specific) Query" test.out > host1_query.out || true
%not-contains: host1_query.out
Query

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Undisposed-object guard: verify no leaked cMessage or cObject at end of run
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
